'''Vertova''' is a ''[[comune]]'' (municipality) in the [[Province of Bergamo]] in the [[Italy|Italian]] region of [[Lombardy]], located about 70 km northeast of [[Milan]] and about 20 km northeast of [[Bergamo]]. As of [[31 December]] [[2004]], it had a population of 4,793 and an area of 15.8 km<U+00B2>.<ref name="istat">All demographics and other statistics: Italian statistical institute [[Istat]].</ref>

The municipality of Vertova contains the ''[[frazione]]'' (subdivision) Semonte.

Vertova borders the following municipalities: [[Casnigo]], [[Colzate]], [[Cornalba]], [[Costa di Serina]], [[Fiorano al Serio]], [[Gazzaniga]], [[Oneta]].


